  "final_answer": "For leg pain, a traditional option that may help alleviate symptoms is Heena, which has been mentioned in a Hadith as a remedy for leg pain, as advised by Rasoolullah. According to Hazrat Salma Umme Rafe’, Rasoolullah advised cupping for headache and Heena for leg pain. However, it's essential to note that the dosage information for Heena is not available, so it's crucial to consult a healthcare professional before using it.\n\nHeena has been traditionally used for leg pain, but its preparation method and dosage are not specified. It's also linked to various chemical compounds, but the exact relationships are not clear.\n\nPlease consult a healthcare professional before using any remedies to ensure safe and effective treatment for your leg pain. They can help you determine the best course of treatment and provide guidance on how to use Heena or other options safely.",
